article.headline: Wyoming 93, Sacramento St. 70
article.story: LARAMIE, Wyo. -- Sean Ogirri scored 25 points as Wyoming defeated Sacramento State 93-70 on Saturday. Wyoming (9-1) overcame a one-point deficit with an 18-4 run to begin the second half and rolled to the win. Ogirri, who hit 7 of 13 3-pointers, was one of five Cowboys to score in double figures, with Brandon Ewing and Afam Muojeke adding 20 points each and Tyson Johnson and Djibril Thiam both scoring 11 for Wyoming. Antonio Flaggs led Sacramento State (1-9) with 23 points, followed by Loren Heath with 19. The Hornets led 37-36 at halftime, but were outscored 57-33 in the second half.
